name: Fellow Knowledge Sharing - Deep Dive on SLAM: Simultaneous Localization And Mapping with Prof. Doc. Cyrill Stachniss
description:
Deep Dive on SLAM - Simultaneous Localization and Mapping
Deep Dive on SLAM - Simultaneous Localization and Mapping:
Maps and accurate position information is a key prerequisite for autonomous navigation. Thus, SLAM is a problem that nearly all autonomous vehicles need to solve to navigate through the world. 
We will discuss a popular approach to tackle SLAM.

name: Codam Masterclass: Introduction to Rust [REMOTE]
description:
LIVE-STREAM: https://youtu.be/fNjMRdlSZ3c


ASK YOUR QUESTIONS DURING THE SESSION HERE: https://wall.sli.do/event/7E9nFMatxGwoLVyRP6c7qG?section=0d1df849-d6b2-40bc-88c3-eb727158c751


ABOUT THE SESSION:

Rust empowers individuals and organizations to build reliable and fast Software. This talk will outline which properties of the Rust language help error prone Humans to tackle complex Engineering problems without drowning in Bugs.


ABOUT SPEAKER:

Markus Klein leads the engineering team at Aleph Alpha. He has a passion for learning and explaining things related to Software Engineering. Working as a C++ Programmer for most of his career, Rust peaked his interest and he started building a Rust Community at his former employeer Blue Yonder. Since then the majority of his Open Source work has shifted to Rust and he is the author of several popular Rust crates. He also finds it strange to write about himself in third person.


ABOUT COMPANY:

Aleph Alpha is the only European company researching, developing and operationalizing a new generation of AI technology for the public and private sector.
